latestPosts.caption:
Yesterday was an unforgettable experience with @reddysameera Mam ! ✨ 

As a makeup artist, working with an Indian film icon was a dream come true. I won’t lie—I was a little nervous, but I gave my absolute best, staying connected with her at every step to make sure she was comfortable and happy. 💄

When everything came together, I honestly couldn’t believe how amazing it turned out. The biggest reward came when she genuinely loved the makeup and flooded me with compliments. 🙏 Her kindness and words of encouragement were more than I could ever ask for. 

And the best part? She said she’d vouch for me! 🥹 As someone who grew up admiring her performances, this meant the world to me. 

I’m beyond grateful for this opportunity and so thankful that she trusted me with her look. A huge thank you for believing in me and for such a beautiful experience. 💕 

#Grateful #MakeupArtistLife #DreamComeTrue #Blessed #MakeupMagic #makeupbydivyanagaraj

latestPosts.caption:
Happy 61st Birthday to the woman who’s been everything and more for me.👑❤️

Last year, I planned something special for her 60th a cake, a little decor, and all my love wrapped into one moment. She had just retired after years of working nonstop, yet she never once missed a beat as a mother. She showed up for me every single time. Through childhood, through every phase of life ,she was there so strong❤️❤️

Even today, she still makes sure I eat well cooking the most amazing meals, often just for me, on days I don’t even ask. She’ll spend hours in the kitchen just to see me nourished, cared for, and loved. That’s who she is. That’s always been her love language.

She’s been my strength, my comfort, my home.
Happy 61st, Maa. You’re not just my mother , you’re my everything. 💕
